1
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:12,400
<i> Lieutenant Conde!</i>

2
00:00:12,533 --> 00:00:13,667
<i> I'm going to arrest you!</i>

3
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,700
<i>I'm unarmed.
You can't arrest me anymore.</i>

4
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:16,467
<i> Cuff him.</i>

5
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:17,867
<i> I said...</i>

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:18,800
<i> He got beaten up.</i>

7
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:20,233
<i> How many did he fight off?</i>

8
00:00:20,367 --> 00:00:21,833
<i>- Just one, Sir.
- Sir Tonyo?</i>

9
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:23,533
<i>Let's say he was
involved in that.</i>

10
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:24,533
<i> Isn't he rich?</i>

11
00:00:24,667 --> 00:00:25,833
<i> He's running, right?</i>

12
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:26,967
<i> By the way, how's our budget?</i>

13
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,067
<i> That's all good.</i>

14
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,300
<i> Literally in the bag.</i>

15
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:30,333
<i>You really are something, boss.</i>

16
00:00:30,467 --> 00:00:32,100
<i>You should be running
for vice mayor.</i>

17
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:34,633
<i>He's waiting for Faye
to be his running mate.</i>

18
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,200
<i> Well, are we threatened?</i>

19
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:37,267
<i>He said he didn't want
any trouble?</i>

20
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:38,633
<i>Sir.
That's enough.</i>

21
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:40,400
<i>Are you sure you don't want
to be in the service anymore?</i>

22
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:41,767
<i>Conde, the chief's calling you.</i>

23
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:43,300
<i> You can't join Garcia's team.</i>

24
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:44,533
<i> With all due respect, Sir,</i>

25
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:46,867
<i> I'm a cop who lost his family!</i>

26
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,600
<i>Pull yourself together,
for Lara.</i>

27
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,033
<i>- Sir.
- What are you doing here?</i>

28
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:51,267
<i>Sir, there's something
you need to know.</i>

29
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,433
<i> Good thing you came, Enriquez.</i>

30
00:00:52,567 --> 00:00:53,600
<i> I need police visibility</i>

31
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:55,200
<i> for the campaign tomorrow.</i>

32
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:56,200
<i>But, Sir...
That's an order.</i>

33
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:57,167
<i> You're dismissed.</i>

34
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:58,767
<i> If it weren't for me, maybe...</i>

35
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:00,667
<i>Maybe Lara's already
about to give birth.</i>

36
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:03,367
<i>Your problem is
you meddle too much.</i>

37
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,833
<i>So can you please
stop coming near me?</i>

38
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:12,433
<i> Tonyo! This room's a mess!</i>

39
00:02:12,567 --> 00:02:15,267
<i>You're so annoying, is this look
like a laundry area?</i>

40
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:18,133
<i> Why are you filming me?</i>

41
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:22,167
<i>Because you look so beautiful
when you're mad.</i>

42
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:23,833
<i>You're unbelievable.
Stop that.</i>

43
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:25,200
<i>- Your style's so lame!
- Look at that!</i>

44
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,800
<i>- Look at that!
- What? Look at that.</i>

45
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:27,800
<i> So beautiful!</i>

46
00:02:27,933 --> 00:02:29,900
<i>You're messing with my mood
again!</i>

47
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:31,000
<i> Fix this!</i>

48
00:02:31,133 --> 00:02:32,100
<i> Come on...</i>

49
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:34,733
<i>Does this even look like
a laundry area, Tonyo?</i>

50
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:49,700
He's so mad at me, Grandmother.

51
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:53,000
He even told me not to come
near him anymore.

52
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,067
Just try to understand.

53
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:03,233
He's grieving.

54
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,533
Here, Bobby, have some water.

55
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:09,933
- Thank you.
You know, Captain's right.

56
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:13,433
That's probably why
he's so irritable with you.

57
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:18,600
I just want things to be okay
between us at the precinct,

58
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:21,867
especially since
he's my superior.

59
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:24,933
Maybe try to win him over?

60
00:03:25,433 --> 00:03:27,733
Oh my, Captain...

61
00:03:27,867 --> 00:03:29,833
now that's a winning suggestion.

62
00:03:29,967 --> 00:03:32,700
Us guys deserve to be wooed too!

63
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:33,867
That's right, Bobby.

64
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,033
Us men love it when
we're the ones being pursued.

65
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:38,433
It's our weakness.
Right, Bro?

66
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:39,900
That's true.

67
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:41,900
Just try it.

68
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,433
Oh, Sir...

69
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,767
I brought you a snack.

70
00:05:05,567 --> 00:05:07,167
I cooked it myself.

71
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:13,433
Hey, Conde!

72
00:05:13,567 --> 00:05:15,033
Hey!

73
00:05:15,767 --> 00:05:18,100
Enriquez, what now?

74
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:20,767
You don't need to go through Bok
for this kind of thing.

75
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:22,233
You're really something.

76
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:25,133
You could've just come
straight to me.

77
00:05:25,267 --> 00:05:26,467
She's something else, Bok.

78
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,100
Really something...

79
00:05:28,233 --> 00:05:30,633
A different palabok.

80
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:33,567
So this one has a different
strategy after all, Bok.

81
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,500
Thanks, Enriquez.

82
00:05:35,633 --> 00:05:36,700
Sure thing, Sir.

83
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:38,467
Anytime.

84
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:41,100
Enriquez is really different,
right?

85
00:05:41,567 --> 00:05:43,233
She even goes through you.

86
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:51,400
Bok...

87
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,767
You smell like chico fruit.

88
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,833
You drank again last night,
didn't you?

89
00:06:04,633 --> 00:06:06,033
This is different, Bok.

90
00:06:06,167 --> 00:06:07,400
This is something else, Bok.

91
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:10,133
Enriquez's way of doing things.

92
00:06:15,033 --> 00:06:17,500
Lieutenant Conde,
can you sign this.

93
00:06:25,767 --> 00:06:26,767
Oh...

94
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:28,800
Sir, here you go.

95
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,233
Grumpy.

96
00:06:39,033 --> 00:06:40,633
What was that?

97
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,133
Nothing, Sir.

98
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,067
Bautista, looks like
nothing's going to happen here.

99
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,133
I'll just go see
Sergeant Enriquez

100
00:06:58,267 --> 00:06:59,100
at the market.

101
00:06:59,233 --> 00:07:00,967
All right,
I've got this covered.

102
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:03,367
I'll head back
to the precinct later.

103
00:07:04,867 --> 00:07:06,100
Hi, guys!

104
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:07,767
Hi to all my viewers!

105
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:11,000
Please share my live, guys!

106
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:13,533
We are live here

107
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:16,133
<i> at Raya Street in Calabari!</i>

108
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:18,200
<i> And if you're around here,</i>

109
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:21,367
<i>please come and support
my dad, okay?</i>

110
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:22,433
<i> Daddy!</i>

111
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:24,067
Okay, oh!

112
00:07:24,733 --> 00:07:26,067
Say hi to my viewers!

113
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,267
<i> Hi!</i>

114
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,800
<i>Let's see each other this
upcoming election, okay?</i>

115
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:31,900
<i>- Yes! Mom!
- Thank you! Thank you!</i>

116
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:35,100
<i>And don't forget
to elect El Hepe!</i>

117
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:37,700
<i>- Thank you very much!
- Thank you very much! Bye.</i>

118
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:41,533
And of course, here is the most
handsome and favorite brother,

119
00:07:41,667 --> 00:07:44,267
<i>the number one councilor of
Calabari.</i>

120
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,833
<i>Oh, you!
Because you have no choice.</i>

121
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:48,867
<i>For those who support us,
thank you very much.</i>

122
00:07:49,033 --> 00:07:51,500
- El Hepe for Mayor, that's it!
- Yes!

123
00:07:53,367 --> 00:07:54,700
- Hello!
- Don't forget.

124
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:55,800
Don't forget.

125
00:07:55,933 --> 00:07:57,000
Hello! Oh...

126
00:07:57,133 --> 00:07:58,233
- Oh, Vice!
- Mayor!

127
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:00,600
- Oh, what, how are you?
- Good morning, Mayor.

128
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:02,233
- How are you?
- Good.

129
00:08:02,367 --> 00:08:04,100
Ah, my vice.

130
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:05,600
- Vice, good morning.
- Vice.

131
00:08:05,733 --> 00:08:06,533
Yes.

132
00:08:06,667 --> 00:08:09,300
May the best vice mayor win.

133
00:08:09,433 --> 00:08:11,333
Good luck to us
in the upcoming elections.

134
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:13,333
That, that's what
I want to hear!

135
00:08:13,467 --> 00:08:15,433
You compete for the position,

136
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:17,933
but you are still friends.

137
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:19,600
- Of course, Mayor.
- That's what I want.

138
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:21,000
- Oh, by the way, Mayor.
- Oh?

139
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:24,000
Amo's group is there.

140
00:08:24,133 --> 00:08:25,067
Oh.

141
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:28,167
Well, maybe you guys
will run into each other.

142
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:30,833
Oh, okay.

143
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:32,967
- Ah, but you know,
- Okay.

144
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:34,433
it's just right for us

145
00:08:34,567 --> 00:08:36,467
to say hello to them.

146
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,433
Yes.

147
00:08:37,567 --> 00:08:39,800
Mayor, Vice, we'll go ahead.

148
00:08:39,933 --> 00:08:40,933
- Okay.
- Good luck, Vice.

149
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:42,667
- Be careful. Okay!
- Good luck.

150
00:09:00,167 --> 00:09:02,733
Amo and El Hepe's supporters are
something else, aren't they?

151
00:09:05,367 --> 00:09:07,967
Oh, you're in a bad mood again,
Ma'am?

152
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:12,700
Leave Lieutenant Conde alone,
Ma'am.

153
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,367
I just wanted to talk to him.

154
00:09:17,867 --> 00:09:20,933
I want to apologize for what
happened in San Isidro.

155
00:09:21,067 --> 00:09:24,767
Ma'am, you're in the same
precinct together.

156
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:27,100
You'll have time to talk to him.

157
00:09:29,167 --> 00:09:30,700
It's up to him.

158
00:09:31,233 --> 00:09:34,633
As long as I'm here, I'll focus
on my investigation of Amo.

159
00:09:34,767 --> 00:09:35,600
That's it!

160
00:09:35,733 --> 00:09:37,367
That's great, Ma'am!

161
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:40,633
So what are we watching now?

162
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:44,067
Noble, look, see,
there's so many people.

163
00:09:44,533 --> 00:09:46,967
That's what the snatchers
are taking advantage of.

164
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,000
My money's gone.

165
00:09:48,133 --> 00:09:50,667
I need something, man, to drink.

166
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,700
You can't get anything,
this, this, this.

167
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,567
This, this.

168
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,033
- This is perfect, Bro.
- That's great.

169
00:09:56,167 --> 00:09:57,967
- There's a lot of people.
- We hit the jackpot, Bro.

170
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,433
- Wait a minute, not yet.
- Oh, that's it.

171
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,933
There, that's it!

172
00:10:09,267 --> 00:10:10,833
My bag!

173
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:12,600
My bag! Help me!

174
00:10:12,733 --> 00:10:14,100
- My bag!
- Oh!

175
00:10:14,233 --> 00:10:15,600
- Mister, what happened?
- My bag!

176
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:17,133
- My pension is there!
- Are you okay?

177
00:10:17,267 --> 00:10:19,500
- Yes!
- Hey, Noble, come on!

178
00:10:20,133 --> 00:10:21,467
- Don't forget, huh?
- Oh, okay.

179
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,067
- Victor Santiago, okay?
- Yes, okay.

180
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,433
I'll count on it. Okay?

181
00:10:24,567 --> 00:10:26,800
- Sir! Oh, how are you?
- Okay, Mayor.

182
00:10:26,933 --> 00:10:27,967
- Victor Santiago, okay?
- Yes, okay.

183
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,100
Oh...

184
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:31,500
Oh, my, this is it!

185
00:10:31,633 --> 00:10:33,700
How are you? How are you all?

186
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:34,667
Oh, there, there.

187
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,000
Well, Oh,

188
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:38,900
that's our neighbors over there.

189
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,700
Oh, hi! How are you?
How are you?

190
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:42,900
Oh, don't forget, okay?

191
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:44,300
Victor Santiago!

192
00:10:44,433 --> 00:10:46,067
- Oh!
- Oh, my!

193
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,867
Oh, yes, oh my...

194
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,033
Oh!

195
00:10:49,167 --> 00:10:50,200
Hello!

196
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,000
How old are you?

197
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:55,967
- Eighty.
- Oh, eighty!

198
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:57,133
- Yes!
- Eighty?

199
00:10:57,267 --> 00:10:58,733
Can I just ask...

200
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:00,167
Do you have a boyfriend now?

201
00:11:02,767 --> 00:11:04,400
You're something else, Amo.

202
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:07,233
You know, I'll definitely vote
for you.

203
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,567
You're my number one.

204
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:10,467
You're my idol!

205
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,433
Thank you. Thank you, thank you.

206
00:11:12,567 --> 00:11:14,833
But always remember this,

207
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:19,133
If I win, you'll all be my
bosses!

208
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:21,667
Oh!

209
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:24,967
Amo! Amo!

210
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:26,100
I'll do it!

211
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:29,667
Amo! Amo! Amo! Amo!

212
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:30,767
- Thank you!
- There!

213
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,633
Thank you.

214
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:34,467
Oh, don't forget, okay?

215
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,000
- Thank you!
- It might...

216
00:11:36,133 --> 00:11:38,967
Ah, Amo, as we expected,

217
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:42,000
we'll cross paths
with El Hepe's group.

218
00:11:42,167 --> 00:11:43,267
Oh, good!

219
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,933
So I can greet my old friend!

220
00:11:46,067 --> 00:11:48,800
Where? Here? All right.

221
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:54,167
Oh.

222
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:56,500
Vince! Vince!

223
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:58,133
You're having a food trip there,
ah! That's delicious!

224
00:11:58,267 --> 00:11:59,467
Why you look like that?

225
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:00,067
It is a...

226
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,267
Cardio!

227
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:02,533
- Jogging!
- For Slimming, slimming.

228
00:12:02,667 --> 00:12:04,767
- Cardio, jogging...
- And zumba...

229
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,100
You must be kidding me.

230
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:07,600
Maybe someone is after you
again.

231
00:12:07,733 --> 00:12:08,733
No one is after us.

232
00:12:08,867 --> 00:12:10,600
- Are we politicians?
- So what's in your hand?

233
00:12:10,733 --> 00:12:11,633
- Nothing, this is nothing.
- It's nothing.

234
00:12:11,767 --> 00:12:12,967
It is a...

235
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,333
- Okay, give it to me.
- We have change, right?

236
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,567
- Let me see. What?.
- Why will I give you this.

237
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,433
- This is important...
- What?

238
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:20,167
Requirements, Bro, requirements.

239
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:22,000
- Requirements, we will have...
- You fools!

240
00:12:22,133 --> 00:12:23,833
Hands up!

241
00:12:23,967 --> 00:12:25,200
We're dead.

242
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,000
We got caught!

243
00:12:36,633 --> 00:12:38,767
What's that? Stop it!

244
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:41,867
Noble, bring them in!

245
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,767
- Go on!
- Come on, come on.

246
00:12:44,433 --> 00:12:46,833
After you made me chase you
earlier...

247
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:59,033
Sir, can I talk to you?

248
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:02,067
About what? San Isidro?

249
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:10,933
I hope you can forgive me.

250
00:13:12,867 --> 00:13:14,700
Because of me, that happened
to your girlfriend.

251
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:17,067
It's not your fault, Sergeant.

252
00:13:19,067 --> 00:13:23,367
Lara died because
I didn't save her.

253
00:13:24,333 --> 00:13:26,300
It's as simple as that.

254
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:29,700
I have a theory.

255
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,333
The Chief didn't include me

256
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:41,267
in Lieutenant Garcia's
Investigation Group.

257
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:43,467
But if you want,
we can work together...

258
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,133
Thank you, Sergeant,

259
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:48,433
but I prefer to work alone.

260
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:01,200
Keep your emotions in check,
okay?

261
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,167
Don't make a scene.

262
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,467
Don't worry!

263
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,833
What's with you?

264
00:14:05,967 --> 00:14:08,133
We just want to have a friendly
banter.

265
00:14:08,267 --> 00:14:10,133
Anyway that's what people want,

266
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:12,833
the two of us face to face.

267
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:15,233
Oh, hi!

268
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:18,533
I know you, I know you.

269
00:14:18,667 --> 00:14:20,300
Control yourself.

270
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:22,567
There are a lot of people now.

271
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:34,667
- Buddy!
- Buddy.

272
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:37,067
Selena.

273
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,700
- Godfather.
- Glen.

274
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,167
How are you?

275
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:44,367
Buddy, you look really tired.

276
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:46,267
Can you still run?

277
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,633
I'm sorry, Buddy.

278
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:52,900
I just don't like seeing my
supporters out in the sun,

279
00:14:53,033 --> 00:14:55,033
while I have an umbrella.

280
00:14:55,567 --> 00:14:59,933
Maybe you're allergic
to the sun, right?

281
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:04,633
Godfather Victor,
long time no see.

282
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:05,900
How are you?

283
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:09,067
Here, who would think
we'd meet here?

284
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:12,600
It's always good to see you and
your family,

285
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:16,067
especially
my good friend Joaquin.

286
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:18,000
Ah, you know, Victor,

287
00:15:18,133 --> 00:15:20,367
people like to see us
face to face.

288
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:24,200
Anyway, in the end,
when the finale comes,

289
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:25,933
it's just the two of us
who will face off.

290
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:29,967
Somehow, I doubt that,
best friend.

291
00:15:30,467 --> 00:15:32,233
What do you mean?

292
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:37,200
You're going to mention
Calabari's crime rate again?

293
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:38,967
Why not?

294
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:42,100
That's what our countrymen want,

295
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:48,900
a peaceful and quiet Calabari.

296
00:15:49,433 --> 00:15:52,600
Dude, for your information,

297
00:15:52,733 --> 00:15:56,967
that's just one of the many
resposibilties of a mayor,

298
00:15:57,100 --> 00:16:00,300
peace and order.

299
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:01,833
You know, Buddy...

300
00:16:01,967 --> 00:16:04,300
I can't blame you...

301
00:16:04,533 --> 00:16:07,600
because you're new to politics.

302
00:16:08,767 --> 00:16:10,767
You already know.

303
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:13,067
You're still in grade one.

304
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:15,433
You have no experience.

305
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,767
Well, that's true.

306
00:16:19,367 --> 00:16:24,433
All I know is that corruption is
linked to the crime rate.

307
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:27,433
That's why I really
want to fight it

308
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:29,233
because that's the root

309
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:32,267
of our people's poverty.

310
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:36,533
You know, that's what I can give
our countrymen...

311
00:16:36,667 --> 00:16:39,667
protection against corruption.

312
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,200
And you're right

313
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:43,767
that I don't have any experience

314
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:46,967
because I don't have any
experience with corruption.

315
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:49,267
What do you mean, Victor?

316
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:53,767
Anyway, Victor,
it was really nice seeing you.

317
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:55,200
We'll go ahead.

318
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:57,033
Same here.

319
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:59,433
You can open those
umbrellas again

320
00:16:59,567 --> 00:17:01,233
because my buddy is feeling hot.

321
00:17:01,367 --> 00:17:03,533
He is exposed to the sun.

322
00:17:04,067 --> 00:17:05,667
Oh, we'll go ahead of you.

323
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:07,067
All right.

324
00:17:19,933 --> 00:17:21,633
Close the umbrellas!

325
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:30,900
Initially, the wife's argument
was self-defense,

326
00:17:31,033 --> 00:17:35,033
but my latest lead smells of
premeditated murder.

327
00:17:35,733 --> 00:17:37,900
Do you know what the lead is,
Tonyo?

328
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,333
Tonyo?

329
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:44,500
- Sir, ah...
- Oh, the San Isidro case,

330
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:46,200
fix it.

331
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:48,033
Let's study that so...

332
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,100
Excuse me,

333
00:17:49,233 --> 00:17:50,767
We can finish it.

334
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:52,400
Garcia...

335
00:17:53,167 --> 00:17:57,000
how's your investigation with
Robles about San Isidro going?

336
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:03,700
Bok, you're so obvious
with your moves.

337
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:06,467
You're just fishing
for the latest.

338
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:10,900
But okay, since we're close.

339
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:14,933
This is just between us.

340
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,667
We have new information,

341
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:21,167
but I can't share it with you.

342
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:25,633
Bok, just to be clear,

343
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:28,467
I'm not taking credit from you.

344
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,533
What I'm saying is,

345
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:32,600
I can be one of your staff.

346
00:18:32,733 --> 00:18:34,067
Give me a task.

347
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:38,800
I'll do anything and the results
will be yours.

348
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:41,633
Anything?

349
00:18:41,767 --> 00:18:45,300
Do you mean, if I order you
to go somewhere,

350
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,867
you'll report back to me
afterward?

351
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,100
Anything, I'll do it.

352
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:52,800
Conde...

353
00:18:52,933 --> 00:18:55,133
you just got back and you're
already being stubborn.

354
00:18:56,433 --> 00:18:58,367
Chief won't like that.

355
00:19:02,567 --> 00:19:05,500
They don't need to know, Robles.

356
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:10,200
Excuse me, Conde.

357
00:19:10,667 --> 00:19:12,967
We are just following the
Chief's protocols?

358
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:17,333
I'm leaving, Garcia.

359
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:24,300
Never mind him, Bok.

360
00:19:24,433 --> 00:19:27,633
He's not eating rice
that's why he's hot-headed.

361
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:29,467
He is taking care of his
jawline.

362
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,367
Come in!

363
00:19:45,233 --> 00:19:46,700
Chief.

364
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:49,133
We caught three snatchers.

365
00:19:49,767 --> 00:19:50,733
Good.

366
00:19:50,867 --> 00:19:52,367
Keep going.

367
00:19:52,867 --> 00:19:53,867
Sir, can I talk to you

368
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,733
about the San Isidro bank
robbery?

369
00:20:02,967 --> 00:20:05,400
What don't you understand,
Sergeant?

370
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,200
I just don't understand, Sir,

371
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:10,433
why you don't want
to accept my help.

372
00:20:10,567 --> 00:20:12,733
No one here is even
listening to me.

373
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:16,400
I understand, Chief,

374
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:19,400
that I can't be directly
involved in the case.

375
00:20:19,867 --> 00:20:22,367
But I hope you'll listen
to my theory.

376
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,933
You know, Sergeant,

377
00:20:26,067 --> 00:20:30,300
we can't base on an old movie.

378
00:20:31,167 --> 00:20:34,767
But, Sir, I went back
to the museum.

379
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,400
The night the robbery happened,

380
00:20:37,533 --> 00:20:40,900
the masks that Amo used in the
movie were also stolen,

381
00:20:41,033 --> 00:20:42,733
the same masks that were used

382
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:45,633
in the San Isidro bank robbery
the next day!

383
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:49,800
There are so many holes
in this case, Sir.

384
00:20:50,433 --> 00:20:52,267
Let's start with...

385
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:56,167
why wasn't there a police report
on the stolen masks.

386
00:20:56,300 --> 00:20:57,933
Okay, Sergeant.

387
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:01,933
I'll throw your info at Garcia.

388
00:21:02,067 --> 00:21:06,300
Now, if they use it or not,
it's their call.

389
00:21:06,433 --> 00:21:10,100
But for now,
nothing will change.

390
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:15,600
You still can't join the case
until I say so.

391
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,300
Do you understand, Sergeant?

392
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:21,100
- But, Sir...
- Do you understand, Sergeant?

393
00:21:21,633 --> 00:21:23,100
You can go.

394
00:21:23,567 --> 00:21:25,333
Yes, Sir.

395
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:44,400
Boss...

396
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:46,300
looks like you guys
didn't get enough

397
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:47,967
at San Isidro Bank.

398
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:49,867
It's really not enough.

399
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,100
Do you know

400
00:21:51,233 --> 00:21:53,967
that the moment you're satisfied
with your income,

401
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:56,467
that's when your progress
will stop.

402
00:21:58,933 --> 00:22:01,667
Hey, guys,
are you sure about that?

403
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,100
Boss, come on...

404
00:22:03,233 --> 00:22:05,433
I brought fire crackers

405
00:22:08,633 --> 00:22:11,733
Go ahead, you know
what you need to do.

406
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,300
Let's go.

407
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,467
Sir, good afternoon!

408
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:25,167
El Helpe! El Hepe, El Hepe!

409
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:27,000
You guys take care of the
upcoming elections.

410
00:22:27,133 --> 00:22:29,167
Got it, okay, huh?

411
00:22:29,567 --> 00:22:31,533
- Okay!
- Daddy, Mommy, I'm just going

412
00:22:31,667 --> 00:22:33,200
to go see your other supporters.

413
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:34,600
I'm just going to go live too.

414
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:36,033
- Oh, okay, okay.
- Oh, okay, okay.

415
00:22:36,167 --> 00:22:37,233
Be careful, Faye, okay?
- Take care!

416
00:22:37,367 --> 00:22:38,367
- Thank you.
- Oh, okay, okay.

417
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:39,967
- See you later, bye!
- Be careful, be careful!

418
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:41,433
Mayor!

419
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:43,267
- Oh?
- Mayor, it's Ms. Ruth,

420
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:44,367
the leader of the women
of the barangay.

421
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:45,467
- Oh, Ms. Ruth..
- Yes.

422
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:46,933
You take care of us?

423
00:22:47,067 --> 00:22:48,100
Oh, that would be nice.

424
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:51,233
We're not being forgiven and
were suddenly caught.

425
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,500
- Hey, that's Boss Tonyo.
- Hey!

426
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:54,267
- Hey! Boss!
- Boss!

427
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:56,300
Oh, Boss! That's it!

428
00:22:56,433 --> 00:22:57,900
You're heaven-sent, Boss!

429
00:22:58,033 --> 00:23:00,267
- That's right!
- We can get out now!

430
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,567
What are you doing here?

431
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:04,633
Boss, these guys' hands
are itching again.

432
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:05,800
You ordered us to do that!

433
00:23:05,933 --> 00:23:07,633
- You said we'd get them.
- Relax!

434
00:23:07,767 --> 00:23:09,967
You're so stubborn!

435
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:11,500
Boss, what now?

436
00:23:11,633 --> 00:23:13,033
Get us out of here.

437
00:23:13,167 --> 00:23:14,267
We have no money, Boss.

438
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:15,300
No strategy.

439
00:23:15,433 --> 00:23:16,833
Who arrested you?

440
00:23:16,967 --> 00:23:17,867
- There, oh.
- There!

441
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:18,767
That woman.

442
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:21,633
- There, boss, Madam Beautiful.
- Her!

443
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,800
The one behind you,
she's the one.

444
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:25,800
She's so snotty.

445
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:28,700
But boss can handle it, man.

446
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:30,033
Find a way.
We can get out of here.

447
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:31,233
The boss can do it.

448
00:23:31,367 --> 00:23:32,667
Oh, that.

449
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:33,900
She's the one.

450
00:23:34,033 --> 00:23:34,900
She's the one who arrested us.

451
00:23:35,033 --> 00:23:37,100
You can handle it, Boss.

452
00:23:37,233 --> 00:23:38,967
We can get out of here, man.

453
00:23:41,667 --> 00:23:43,767
Okay, guys, we're over here on
this side

454
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:46,067
and we'll interview our
colleagues.

455
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:48,400
- Mister, mister, hello!
- Hello!

456
00:23:48,533 --> 00:23:51,767
So which mayor will you vote
for in this election?

457
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:54,300
Of course, El Hepe!

458
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:58,167
<i> El Hepe! El Hepe! El Hepe!</i>

459
00:23:58,333 --> 00:24:01,233
Thank you!

460
00:24:01,367 --> 00:24:02,733
Mister, Mister!

461
00:24:02,867 --> 00:24:03,900
- There.
- El Hepe! El Hepe! El Hepe!

462
00:24:04,033 --> 00:24:06,500
Which mayor will you vote
for in this election?

463
00:24:06,633 --> 00:24:07,933
El Hepe!

464
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:10,900
The election is coming...

465
00:24:11,033 --> 00:24:14,300
Hey! Mayor! Mayor!

466
00:24:19,633 --> 00:24:21,367
Hello, Sir. Miss Faye
is with us!

467
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:22,467
Miss Faye, come with us.

468
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:23,733
- You'll be safe.
- Come on, come on, let's go!

469
00:24:23,867 --> 00:24:25,133
Come on!

470
00:24:25,267 --> 00:24:26,533
She is with us. Let's go!

471
00:24:26,667 --> 00:24:27,433
- Wait, Mister!
- You're safe with us, Ma'am.

472
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:28,767
Just come with us.

473
00:24:28,933 --> 00:24:29,800
Who are you?

474
00:24:29,933 --> 00:24:30,933
Where are you taking me?

475
00:24:31,067 --> 00:24:31,933
Ma'am, come with us, Ma'am!

476
00:24:32,067 --> 00:24:33,200
- Let me go!
- You're safe with us!

477
00:24:33,333 --> 00:24:34,833
Come with us!

478
00:24:34,967 --> 00:24:36,633
Come with us!

479
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:37,767
- Get her inside!
- Help!

480
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:39,967
Help!

481
00:24:40,467 --> 00:24:41,533
Let's go! Go! Go!

482
00:24:41,667 --> 00:24:43,867
- Let's go!
- Help!

483
00:24:57,567 --> 00:24:59,200
I need to get my daughter back.

484
00:24:59,333 --> 00:25:00,333
We'll do everything.

485
00:25:00,467 --> 00:25:01,833
In the video of the kidnapping,

486
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,533
the name of the kidnapper
was mentioned.

487
00:25:03,667 --> 00:25:05,733
Sebastian Placido alias Batsi.

488
00:25:05,867 --> 00:25:07,433
- Batsi...
- Just a reminder, okay?

489
00:25:07,567 --> 00:25:10,833
No one will move until the
exchange is over.

490
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:12,700
We need to make sure
the victim is safe.

491
00:25:12,833 --> 00:25:14,367
- Copy, Chief.
- It's not a bad idea

492
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:15,867
to follow that lead.

493
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,300
Sir, we might get scolded by...

494
00:25:17,433 --> 00:25:19,433
If you don't want to come,
then don't.

495
00:25:19,567 --> 00:25:22,367
Boss, you know I retired a long
time ago.

496
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:24,400
This is all I'm busy with.

497
00:25:24,533 --> 00:25:26,233
What's with you,
you're too defensive.
